<!-- ── FORMULA ── -->
<section class="content-section reveal">
  <h2>The Formula</h2>
  <p>Stamp Duty Land Tax (SDLT) uses a <strong>progressive band system</strong> — similar to income tax. You don't pay the top rate on the whole price; each band applies only to the portion of the price within that range.</p>
  <div class="formula-box">
    SDLT = &sum; (Portion of Price in Each Band &times; Band Rate)
  </div>

  <h3>Standard SDLT Rates — from 1 April 2025</h3>
  <div class="example-data">
    <div class="example-row"><span class="label">0%</span><span class="value">£0 – £125,000</span></div>
    <div class="example-row"><span class="label">2%</span><span class="value">£125,001 – £250,000</span></div>
    <div class="example-row"><span class="label">5%</span><span class="value">£250,001 – £925,000</span></div>
    <div class="example-row"><span class="label">10%</span><span class="value">£925,001 – £1,500,000</span></div>
    <div class="example-row"><span class="label">12%</span><span class="value">Above £1,500,000</span></div>
  </div>

  <h3>First-Time Buyer Rates</h3>
  <p>Available on properties up to £500,000 where the buyer has never owned a residential property.</p>
  <div class="example-data">
    <div class="example-row"><span class="label">0%</span><span class="value">£0 – £300,000</span></div>
    <div class="example-row"><span class="label">5%</span><span class="value">£300,001 – £500,000</span></div>
  </div>

  <h3>Additional property surcharge</h3>
  <div class="formula-box">
    If you already own a residential property (e.g. buy-to-let or second home), add a <strong>5% surcharge</strong> on top of every band.
  </div>
</section>

